# Multi-agent and subagents

Principle: **delegate work, not responsibility.** The parent session owns workflow state, merge decisions, and verification after parallel work.

## Prompt construction

Do not paste unbounded chat history into subagents. Build prompts from **durable artifacts**: PRD path, OpenSpec change path (if any), `.skillgrid/project/CONTEXT.md` excerpts when relevant, handoff path, event log path, explicit output filenames under `.skillgrid/tasks/research/<change-id>/`, and exact return schema.

Every delegated prompt must include a compact context injection packet:

- objective;
- constraints/non-goals;
- exact task id or slice id;
- owned files and edit boundaries;
- ordered artifact paths to read (including handoff/event/registry);
- expected output path and return format;
- verification command and pass condition.

## Parallelism

Parallelize only when goals are independent, outputs do not collide on the same files without ownership, and the parent can read and merge all results before advancing.

Dependency waves per `docs/08-multi-agent-work.md`: respect `blockedBy` / `unblocks` and failed verification gates downstream.

Sequencing gate before parallel dispatch:

- If any agent needs another agent's output, use sequential dispatch.
- Use parallel dispatch only when tasks are independent and ownership is non-overlapping.

## Forbidden patterns

- Multiple writers on overlapping files without explicit boundaries
- One persona secretly deciding which others to invoke (hidden orchestration)
- Advancing phase while handoff/events omit completed subagent work

## After subagent returns

Read summaries and cited files; reconcile conflicts against PRD/specs/handoff; append or validate event log entries; update handoff with evidence, blockers, and next safe command.
